<% content_for :title, "LocalBaker — Ethos & Mission" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Learn about the ethos and mission behind LocalBaker. We believe in simplicity, web standards, and escaping the bloat." %>

<div class="stack container" style="max-width: 600px; padding-block: var(--sp-lg);">
  <h1 style="font-size: 2rem;">Our Ethos</h1>

  <hr class="divider" style="margin-block: var(--sp-md)" />

  <div class="stack">
    <h2 class="font-bold">1. Keep It Simple</h2>
    <p>
      If you look around the web today, everything feels heavy and complicated. LocalBaker takes a step back. We focus on getting the basics exactly right. The platform is intentionally lightweight, skipping the bloated features that you don't actually need. Just clean, fast, and reliable software that stays out of your way.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-bold">2. Built for Your Kitchen</h2>
    <p>
      You don't need an enterprise inventory management system to bake 20 loaves of sourdough. You just need a simple way to share your menu, let people claim a loaf, and see a clear list of what to bake. We build specifically for this human scale. Everything else is just noise.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-bold">3. No Passwords, No Friction</h2>
    <p>
      Your customers shouldn't have to remember another password just to buy bread. We use magic links and native session management to keep the purchasing experience as smooth as possible. They click your link, pick their items, and check out.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-bold">4. Community Supported</h2>
    <p>
      We believe the best communities are built offline. Our goal is to provide the digital plumbing necessary for you to build real, human connections with your neighbors through the sharing of food.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="panel text-center stack-sm" style="margin-top: var(--sp-lg)">
    <p class="font-bold">Ready to start baking?</p>
    <div>
      <%= link_to "Open your storefront", new_session_path, class: "button primary" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
